"Bedulina D.S., Zimmer M., Timofeyev M.A.","Sub-littoral and supra-littoral amphipods respond differently to acute thermal stress",2010,"Comparative Biochemistry and Physiology - B Biochemistry and Molecular Biology","155","4",,"413","418",,,10.1016/j.cbpb.2010.01.004,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77949332961&partnerID=40&md5=9eb480202a4c95c23e78c892b3dcfcbe","Irkutsk State University, Ul. Karl-Marx 1, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation; Christian-Albrechts-Universität, Zoologisches Institut, Am Botanischen Garten 9, D-24118 Kiel, Germany; Baikalian Research Centre, Ul. Karl-Marx 5-10, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation","Bedulina, D.S., Irkutsk State University, Ul. Karl-Marx 1, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation, Christian-Albrechts-Universität, Zoologisches Institut, Am Botanischen Garten 9, D-24118 Kiel, Germany, Baikalian Research Centre, Ul. Karl-Marx 5-10, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation; Zimmer, M., Irkutsk State University, Ul. Karl-Marx 1, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation; Timofeyev, M.A., Irkutsk State University, Ul. Karl-Marx 1, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation, Christian-Albrechts-Universität, Zoologisches Institut, Am Botanischen Garten 9, D-24118 Kiel, Germany, Baikalian Research Centre, Ul. Karl-Marx 5-10, 664003, Irkutsk, Russian Federation","Thermal tolerance was determined in two closely related amphipod species from contrasting environments (sub-littoral and supra-littoral zones of the sea) using HSP expression and the activity of antioxidant enzymes. The levels of HSP70 and small HSPs present in untreated control animals were higher in the supra-littoral Orchestia gammarellus than in the sub-littoral Gammarus oceanicus. Under the acute thermal stress, HSP levels increased less strongly in O. gammarellus than in G. oceanicus. Activities of antioxidant enzymes peroxidase, catalase and glutathione S-transferase, were more pronounced in the supra-littoral O. gammarellus then in the sub-littoral G. oceanicus. We conclude that the environmental temperature regime modifies key cellular defense mechanisms in amphipods. Higher levels of constitutive HSP synthesis and higher levels of antioxidant enzymes in the supra-littoral species likely reflects adaptation to this highly thermally variable environment. © 2010 Elsevier Inc.","Acute thermal stress; Amphipods; Antioxidant enzymes; Baltic; Heat shock proteins","catalase; glutathione transferase; heat shock protein 70; peroxidase; Amphipoda; article; controlled study; enzyme activity; Gammarus oceanicus; littoral; marine environment; nonhuman; Orchestia gammarellus; priority journal; protein expression; protein synthesis; temperature stress; Amphipoda; Animals; Catalase; Glutathione Transferase; HSP70 Heat-Shock Proteins; Peroxidase; Stress, Physiological; Temperature; Amphipoda; Animalia; Gammarus oceanicus; Orchestia gammarellus",,"catalase, 9001-05-2; glutathione transferase, 50812-37-8; peroxidase, 9003-99-0; Catalase, 1.11.1.6; Glutathione Transferase, 2.5.1.18; HSP70 Heat-Shock Proteins; Peroxidase, 1.11.1.7",,,,"Aebi, H., Catalase in vitro (1984) Meths. Enzymol, 5, pp. 121-126; Arkush, K.D., Cherr, G.N., Clegg, J.S., Induced thermotolerance and tissue Hsc70 in juvenile coho salmon, Oncorhynchus kisutch (2008) Acta Zool, 89, pp. 331-338; Bahrndorff, S., Mariën, J., Loeschcke, V., Ellers, J., Dynamics of heat-induced thermal stress resistance and Hsp70 expression in the springtail, Orchesella cincta (2009) Funct Ecol, 23, pp. 233-239; Bedulina, D.S., Timofeyev, M.A., Zimmer, M., Zwirnmann, E., Menzel, R., Steinberg, C.E.W., Different natural organic matter isolates cause similar stress response patterns in the freshwater amphipod, Gammarus pulex (2010) Environ Sci Pollut Res, 17, pp. 261-269; Bergmeyer, H.U., Methods of enzymatic analysis (1983) VCH Weinheim, (1-12), pp. 648-653; Boston, R.S., Viitanen, P.V., Vierling, E., Molecular chaperones and protein folding in plants (1996) Plant Mol. Biol., 32 (1-2), pp. 191-222; Bradfo